<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-23T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="244" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/396: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-23T17:00:00-06:00">January 23, 1934—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>9. The following telegram has been sent to the Legation in Managua:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“January 23, 5 p.m. Your January 23, 3 [<hi rend="italic">2?</hi>] p.m.<note n="31" xml:id="d244fn31">See last paragraph
                                        of telegram <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Foreign
                                    Office has just notified me that President Ubico agrees to
                                    recognition on January 25 in manner outlined in my 7 [<hi rend="italic">8?</hi>], January 22, 1 p.m. to the
                                    Department.</p>
                                <p>Repeated to Department and Tegucigalpa.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lawton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>